"title": "5577: taxation",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5577: taxation",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Any form of payment levied on people by a supervising authority.</p>\n<h2>Taxation exacted from subject nations</h2>\n<h3>Tribute to Moab</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg3:15\">JDG 3:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg3:17-Judg3:18\">JDG 3:17–3:18</a></p>\n<h3>Tribute to David</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:2\">2SA 8:2</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr18:2\">1CH 18:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:6\">2SA 8:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr18:6\">1CH 18:6</a></p>\n<h3>Tribute to Solomon</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs4:21\">1KI 4:21</a></p>\n<h3>Tribute to Assyria</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:3\">2KI 17:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos10:6\">HOS 10:6</a></p>\n<h3>Tribute to Egypt</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:33\">2KI 23:33</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:3\">2CH 36:3</a></p>\n<h3>Tribute to Judah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr17:11\">2CH 17:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:8\">2CH 26:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa16:1\">ISA 16:1</a></p>\n<h3>Tribute to Persia</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth10:1\">EST 10:1</a></p>\n<h3>Universal tribute</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps72:10\">PSA 72:10</a></strong> <em>Universal tribute means universal reign. This psalm is widely regarded as Messianic.</em></p>\n<h3>Refusal to pay tribute was a sign of rebellion</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:4\">2KI 17:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra4:13\">EZR 4:13</a></p>\n<h2>Taxation for the support of the state</h2>\n<h3>Land tax</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:35\">2KI 23:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:34\">GEN 41:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh5:4\">NEH 5:4</a></p>\n<h2>Census tax</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:11-Exod30:16\">EXO 30:11–30:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:1\">LUK 2:1</a></p>\n<h3>Trade tax</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:14-1Kgs10:15\">1KI 10:14–10:15</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:13-2Chr9:14\">2CH 9:13–9:14</a></p>\n<h3>Such levies may be unjustly burdensome</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:10-1Sam8:18\">1SA 8:10–8:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan11:20\">DAN 11:20</a></p>\n<h2>Covenantal taxation: the tithe</h2>\n<h3>Tithing prescribed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:30-Lev27:33\">LEV 27:30–27:33</a></strong> <em>As part of their covenantal obligations the Israelites were commanded to offer a tenth of their income to the LORD.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:20\">GEN 14:20</a></p>\n<h3>The tithe supported the priests and the poor</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:21\">NUM 18:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:28-Deut14:29\">DEU 14:28–14:29</a></p>\n<h3>The tithe often seems to have been neglected</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:8-Mal3:10\">MAL 3:8–3:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr31:4\">2CH 31:4</a></p>\n<h2>Taxation for the support of the temple</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:24-Matt17:26\">MAT 17:24–17:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr24:4-2Chr24:12\">2CH 24:4–24:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs12:4-2Kgs12:5\">2KI 12:4–12:5</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ and taxation</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ was falsely accused of opposing taxation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:1-Luke23:2\">LUK 23:1–23:2</a></p>\n<h3>He himself paid tax</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:24-Matt17:27\">MAT 17:24–17:27</a></p>\n<h3>He commanded others to pay taxes</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:15-Matt22:22\">MAT 22:15–22:22</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:13-Mark12:17\">MRK 12:13–12:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:20-Luke20:26\">LUK 20:20–20:26</a></p>\n<h2>Believers and taxation</h2>\n<h3>Paying taxes demonstrates submission to God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:1\">ROM 13:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:5-Rom13:6\">ROM 13:5–13:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:13\">1PE 2:13</a></p>\n<h3>Paying taxes should silence unjust criticism</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:3\">ROM 13:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:15\">1PE 2:15</a></p>\n<h3>Paying taxes is reimbursement for services rendered</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:15-Matt22:22\">MAT 22:15–22:22</a> <em>“Give” in verse 21 means “give back as in settlement of a debt”</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:7\">ROM 13:7</a></p>",
